1
00:00:22,760 --> 00:00:23,760
We've been waiting all morning.

2
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:24,840
Who are these people coming?

3
00:00:24,840 --> 00:00:26,600
Seems like they're Manager Wen's enemies.

4
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:27,760
What are you talking about?

5
00:00:27,760 --> 00:00:29,440
Is the live stream camera ready?

6
00:00:29,440 --> 00:00:31,040
I'll get it ready right away.

7
00:00:33,240 --> 00:00:35,200
Wen, are you still waiting?

8
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:37,000
Manager, you're here too.

9
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:39,920
It should be here.

10
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:42,520
Shouldn't I just make a phone call?

11
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:43,320
No.

12
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:44,960
I reported this matter.

13
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:46,490
I should resolve it myself.

14
00:00:47,680 --> 00:00:48,640
All right.

15
00:00:48,640 --> 00:00:50,700
Then I will have a good talk with them.

16
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,160
Let's go.

17
00:00:57,280 --> 00:00:58,680
Sorry to trouble you this time, Manager.

18
00:00:58,680 --> 00:00:59,880
It's what I should do.

19
00:01:01,120 --> 00:01:02,120
They're here.

20
00:01:02,120 --> 00:01:03,440
Start the livestream.

21
00:01:06,760 --> 00:01:07,960
My big star.

22
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:09,440
You're finally here.

23
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:12,640
I have deleted the videos and articles on all accounts

24
00:01:12,960 --> 00:01:14,800
and published a correction notice.

25
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:16,960
The details are written here.

26
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:22,600
Apologizing online

27
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:24,530
and deleting a video to solve this?

28
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:27,000
You're oversimplifying the problem.

29
00:01:27,160 --> 00:01:28,620
Then what else do you want?

30
00:01:29,480 --> 00:01:30,520
Who are you?

31
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:31,840
What does it have to do with you?

32
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:33,759
I think he looks familiar.

33
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:37,280
Anyway,

34
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:39,479
I want you to delete your accounts,

35
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:40,840
quit this industry,

36
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:46,240
and pay 2 million for the company's reputation damage.

37
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:51,600
The fake news did cause reputational damage to the company,

38
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:54,400
but you should be the one paying the compensation.

39
00:01:54,720 --> 00:01:56,120
Me?

40
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:57,280
This fake news

41
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:59,520
cites a lot of internal confidential company information.

42
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:01,200
I've checked, and externally,

43
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,930
this part was only given to you.

44
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:04,280
I remember now.

45
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:06,240
You are the general manager of An'ers Group,

46
00:02:06,240 --> 00:02:07,120
An Yufan.

47
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:11,840
Check it yourselves.

48
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:19,760
Mr. An,

49
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,880
please be the bigger person and forgive us.

50
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:23,480
It was our mistake this time.

51
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,200
As a PR company,

52
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:26,920
you actually took the initiative to leak company secrets

53
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:29,050
and create topics for public opinion.

54
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:31,920
Are you trying to target An'ers Group?

55
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:33,680
No, Mr. An.

56
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:36,079
Our boss is on his way back.

57
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:37,640
This was just an accident.

58
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:38,640
Please give us another chance.

59
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:40,480
You calculated the compensation quite well just now.

60
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:41,960
I'd like to hear

61
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:44,840
how the compensation for breach of contract should be calculated.

62
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:47,040
Mr. An, this is all a misunderstanding.

63
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:49,720
We will definitely provide a solution you're satisfied with.

64
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:51,920
Could we move to the meeting room?

65
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:53,800
This way, please.

66
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:57,640
Wen Lingli,

67
00:02:58,280 --> 00:03:00,080
so many years have passed.

68
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:02,050
Why are you still targeting me?

69
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:04,840
You forgot everything.

70
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:07,580
Of course it's all in the past for you.

71
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:12,800
Lingli.

72
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:14,400
Brother Liang Chen,

73
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:16,040
you're here.

74
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:21,000
Are you going back?

75
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:22,560
Yes.

76
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:25,800
I really didn't expect

77
00:03:26,079 --> 00:03:28,960
that Wang Yu would do something like student loans.

78
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:32,760
I was really out of my mind to believe him.

79
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:34,400
Lingli,

80
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:37,600
you should really control your temper.

81
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:39,900
Don't be so willful in the future.

82
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:41,320
Yeah.

83
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:43,600
Got it, Brother Chen.

84
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,200
Also,

85
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:47,240
I'm leaving too.

86
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,730
Immigrating to Canada with my mom.

87
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:52,200
Actually, we've had this plan for a while,

88
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:55,480
but there just wasn't the right opportunity.

89
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:58,079
After everything that's happened,

90
00:03:58,840 --> 00:03:59,970
I've figured it out.

91
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:02,160
I won't run away anymore.

92
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,200
Then,

93
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:06,840
after you go abroad,

94
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:09,160
will you come back?

95
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:10,960
I don't know yet.

96
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:14,410
But it doesn't matter anymore.

97
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:17,880
I'm leaving.

98
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:32,170
Who says it doesn't matter?

99
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:36,890
It seems that this time,

100
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:39,240
you still won.

101
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:01,280
It really is you.

102
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:03,580
You looked familiar just now.

103
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:05,100
Don't you remember me?

104
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,640
Hi, Zixi.

105
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:07,840
Long time no see.

106
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:12,410
Do you still remember this?

107
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:13,650
Why do you have this?

108
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:17,160
It seems I guessed right.

109
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:18,440
You were the one

110
00:05:18,440 --> 00:05:20,240
who hid it, right?

111
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:21,520
I...

112
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:34,760
Did you just see Yang Qian?

113
00:05:34,880 --> 00:05:35,680
Yes.

114
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:38,000
But that doesn't matter anymore.

115
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:38,920
What matters is

116
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:41,280
that we are reunited.

117
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:44,159
Come with me somewhere.

118
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:53,240
Why are you back at school?

119
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:56,800
No one uses this anymore.

120
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:03,220
When I came back to school,

121
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:05,260
you had already forgotten me.

122
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,400
I often stayed here alone,

123
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:10,960
recalling everything we had been through.

124
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,440
I remembered how we met.

125
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:17,250
I remembered how we got to know each other.

126
00:06:17,280 --> 00:06:20,240
And I remembered what I always wanted to say to you.

127
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:35,200
I wonder if you still remember this secret code.

128
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,080
Uncle He.

129
00:06:55,159 --> 00:06:56,560
Uncle He is really something.

130
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:58,560
He knew all along but didn't tell me.

131
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:02,130
He probably planned to tell you at the right time.

132
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:04,080
The boss said to give this to you.

133
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:05,720
He said the room is only cleaned occasionally

134
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:07,650
and has been kept exactly as it was.

135
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,800
The room hasn't changed.

136
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:20,720
Wait a minute.

137
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:48,200
Okay.

138
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,260
I've been waiting for you for a long time.

139
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:08,210
Happy birthday.

140
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:36,200
Where did this diary come from?

141
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:38,320
It's probably magic.

142
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:40,360
Miss.

143
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:41,280
Over here.

144
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:43,280
Wow, your books are so new.

145
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:43,720
Yeah.

146
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:46,040
My daughter graduated from college and probably doesn't want to read them anymore.

147
00:09:46,040 --> 00:09:46,920
Oh wow.

148
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:49,660
That's a diary, right?

149
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:50,360
Yes.

150
00:09:50,520 --> 00:09:51,160
Oh.

151
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,520
Assistant Casting Director Xi Chongjing

152
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:08,440
Props Assistant Li Kunxiao

153
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:10,360
Production Vehicle Yi Mingle

154
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:12,240
Yitong
